DATELINE: KINGS MOUNTAIN, NORTH CAROLINA

Cindy Scoggins Stone

Cindy Scoggins Stone, 60, of Kings Mountain, NC, passed away on May 21, 2020 at Wendover Hospice in Shelby, NC. Born in Rutherford County, NC, she was the daughter of the late Bobby Norris Scoggins. She was also preceded in death by a sister, Julia Elaine Scoggins. Cindy loved her family and her dog Dusty. She especially enjoyed attending her grandsonâ€™s band concerts. She enjoyed traveling to the beach, working Sudoku puzzles, and loved cooking for her family. She also enjoyed helping her sister with home improvements and she loved making jewelry. She was greatly loved and will be missed by her family and friends. The family would like to express their sincere appreciation to Hospice of Cleveland County for their care and especially to Chaplain Janice Cooper. Memorial contributions can be made to Hospice of Cleveland County, 951 Wendover Heights Dr, Shelby, NC 28150.

SURVIVORS:

1 Son: Timothy Steven Stone and wife Kimberly Heather Ann Stone, Shelby, NC;

Mother: Mattie Gettys Scoggins; Kings Mountain, NC;

2 Brothers: Samuel Jefferson Scoggins and wife Patsy, Ellenboro, NC;

Andy Scoggins and wife Robin, Kings Mountain, NC;

1 Sister: Janice Sachs and husband Dave, Charlotte, NC;

1 Grandson: Timothy Steven Stone, II, Shelby, NC;

Nephews: Eric and Evan Sachs

Nieces: Katelyn Latham and Catherine Scoggins

FUNERAL SERVICE: The family will hold a private service

GUEST REGISTER AVAILABLE AT WWW.HARRISFUNERALS.COM

